<subSubSection id="C32F7CE99664FFF5FF10F919DCDAF8FA" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8A2F629664FFF5FF10F919DCDAF8FA" blockId="6.[151,1436,1585,1838]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B941F3709664FFF5FF10F919D935F8DE" bold="true" box="[199,335,1777,1802]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Comments.</emphasis>
Unlike most of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3554E19664FFF5FDCEF919DAEDF8DD" box="[537,663,1777,1801]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941F3709664FFF5FDCEF919DAEDF8DD" box="[537,663,1777,1801]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Berlandina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, which inhabit arid habitats (steppe and various 
<typeStatus id="548E91C09664FFF5FAE9F91ADD03F8DE" box="[1342,1401,1778,1802]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">types</typeStatus>
of deserts), the new species is found also in the wet riparian forest subject to periodic flooding.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
